Mammoth Brewing Co.:
Sunday – Thursday: 10am – 9pm*
Friday & Saturday: 10am – 9:30pm*

The EATery:
Daily: 11:00am – Close

*Closing times are subject to early closures during shoulder seasons

Reservations: We do not take reservations.

Welcome to MBC & The EATery

We’ve been obsessively crafting beers since 1995. We pioneer, curious and unfaltering, determined not to stop until we achieve mouth-watering perfection, often at the expense of reasonable bedtimes and our social lives. Pulling inspiration from our natural surroundings, we boldly blend the best of our local ingredients with the know-how we’ve picked up from years of brewing award-winning beer.

Our brewery, tasting room, beer garden, and retail store are located at 18 Lake Mary Road, at the corner of Main Street & Minaret Road in Mammoth Lakes. The EATery is located in the tasting room, supplying amazing beer-centric food by chef Brandon Brocia. Check out The EATery menu here. Savor a pint and a bite to eat, sample a tasting flight, pick up a 6-pack, fill your growler, and enjoy the mountain views and friendly atmosphere.

Your well-behaved, leashed pupper is welcome in our outdoor beer garden. No barking, biting, or begging, and don't leave your trail buddy unattended.

Fun events include live music and Trivia Night, and we also host private events. See our Events page for more information.

title: Mammoth Lakes Museum
description:
Our Hours

June-september: 10 AM to 6 PM

Open Monday-Sunday, closed on Wednesdays

We are open six days a week Memorial Weekend through the end of September.

Other Information

Fees: FREE! A $5.00 donation is suggested & memberships are appreciated.

ADA Accessibility: Access is available for those who park on the lawn near the disabled placard and enter through the kitchen (back door) on the ramp.

Eco-Friendly: Connected to the town’s bike trails in Mammoth Lakes.

Pet Friendly:  Pets should be leashed on the museum grounds per the Town of Mammoth Lakes and the U.S. Forest Service leash laws. Service animals only are welcome inside the museum. We provide kennels a.k.a “doggie dorms” outside for non-service animals. Please clean up after your pets!
